<p style="padding-left: 150px; padding-right: 150px;" class="w3-justify">This thesis aims to build a dynamic survey management system . Routine and repetitive surveys require a sophisticated and structured approach to the execution of the survey and the management and reporting of survey response data. Well designed, robust and repeatable automated processes can take the grind out of handling survey datasets - improving quality and reducing cost on a daily basis. A system which aims to build a web-enabled application, a Survey management system, which empowers the development, distributing and analysis of survey forms to improve communication, process management, and decision support across the organizations is necessary for this business need.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 150px; padding-right: 150px;" class="w3-justify">The built system is based on Web, which allows users to design, public forms of question and collect reports for any purpose. Survey Management System is developed based on backgrounds of asp.net and javascript. The application brings to users many features ensuring it is a convenient environment.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 150px; padding-right: 150px; padding-bottom: 200px;" class="w3-justify">The objective of this thesis is to build a web-based system which applies the dynamically developed data structure to allow to create various surveys easily. And further, the thesis is to develop a supporting decision system.  The system plans to bring to users following features, Question Management, Survey Design, Survey Distribution, Access Management, Analytical Reports. Furthermore, the thesis supports some external methods for evolution in the future as Scoring, Graph Report. The topic expects to apply the framework designed during the thesis term to increase reality value of use.</p>